net.dempsy.lifecycle.annotation.internal

Class AnnotatedMethodInvoker

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.lifecycle.annotation.internal.AnnotatedMethodInvoker

  • public class AnnotatedMethodInvoker
extends Object
    This class will identify and invoke annotated methods, maintaining a thread-safe cache of those methods. It currently supports the following three scenarios (which have disjoint constructors):
    • A single annotated getter method.
      The invokeGetter(java.lang.Object) method will look for an annotated no-parameter method on an arbitrary object, and invoke that method. Behavior is undefined if there are multiple methods with the same annotation.
    • Multiple annotated setter methods.
      The invokeSetter(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object) method will look for annotated methods on a single class that take one parameter of a "compatible" type to its argument. If there is no method that takes the exact type, it will walk the class hierarchy of its argument to find a matching type.
    • Multiple annotated single argument methods.
      The invokeMethod(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object) method will look for annotated methods on a single class that take a single parameter of a "compatible" type as its argument. If there is no method that takes the exact type, it will walk the class hierarchy of its argument to find a matching type.
    Separate instances must be constructed for these each scenario, as they're based on different data.

        public boolean isValueSupported(Object value)
